bama Athletics|pages=9\u201313}}</ref>\n\n{{Col-begin}}\n{{Col-3}}\n\n====Offense====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Player\n! Class\n! Position\n|-\n| [[Jalen Hurts]]\n| Sophomore\n| Quarterback \n|-\n| [[Damien Harris]]\n| Junior\n| Running back\n|-\n| [[Calvin Ridley]]\n| Junior\n| Wide receiver \n|-\n| [[Ross Pierschbacher]]\n| R-Junior \n| Guard\n|-\n| [[Bradley Bozeman]]\n| R-Senior\n| Center\n|-\n| [[Jonah Williams]]\n| Sophomore\n| Tackle\n|}\n{{Col-3}}\n\n====Defense====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-;\n! Player\n! Class\n! Position\n|-\n| [[Tony Brown (defensive back, born 1995)|Tony Brown]]\n| Senior\n| Cornerback\n|-\n| [[Anthony Averett]]\n| R-Senior\n| Cornerback\n|-\n| [[Minkah Fitzpatrick]]\n| Junior\n| Safety \n|-\n| [[Shaun Dion Hamilton]]\n| Senior\n| Linebacker\n|-\n| [[Ronnie Harrison]]\n| Junior\n| Safety\n|-\n| [[Daron Payne]]\n| Junior\n| Defensive tackle\n|}\n{{Col-3}}\n\n====Special teams====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-;\n! Player\n! Class\n! Position\n|-\n| [[JK Scott]]\n| Senior\n| Punter\n|}\n{{Col-3}}\n{{Col-end}}\n\n===Spring game===\n{{AFB game box start\n|Title= 2017 A-Day Spring Game\n|Visitor= White\n|V1= 14\n|V2= 7\n|V3= 0\n|V4= 3\n|Host= Crimson\n|H1= 7\n|H2= 10\n|H3= 0\n|H4= 10\n|Location= Tuscaloosa, Alabama\n|StartTime= \n|TimeZone= Central\n|ElapsedTime= \n|Attendance= \n|Weather= \n|Referee= \n|TVAnnouncers= \n|TVStation= ESPN\n}}\n{{AFB game box end}}\nAlabama's annual A-Day spring game was held on April 22, 2017. Kicker [[JK Scott]] kicked a field goal as time expired to win the game for the [[Jalen Hurts]]-led Crimson team over the [[Tua Tagovailoa]]-led White team.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2705179-crimson-outlast-white-27-24-in-2017-alabama-spring-game-as-tide-look-to-reload|title=Crimson Outlasts White 27-24 in 2017 Alabama Spring Game as Tide Look to Reload|date=April 22, 2017|website=Bleacher Report|first=Tim|last=Daniels}}</ref>\n{{clear}}\n\n==Schedule==\n{{CFB schedule\n| rankyear = 2017\